line_2: Autumn leaves dance to the ground,
Golden leaves dance to the ground,
In the chaos of the day,
Horns blare, footsteps rush and dance
Bugs still hide in the dark
Dreams weave through the silent sky,
Birds are singing their sweet song
Dust motes dance in sun's bright ray,
Leaves dance under a pale moon,
Saffron threads weave through warm broth
Bugs are squashed, the program runs,
Silver ripples dance and gleam bright
Wakes the mind and body up,
